parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration when braking
vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
engine revving up when stepping on the brake pedal
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle fails to respond when the brake pedal is depressed
the engine revs when the brake pedal is depressed
the emergency brake must be applied to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fractured steering shaft can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle sways to one side without warning
the steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often when tapping the brake pedal or pressing the accelerator pedal
and can only be stopped by turning off the ignition or shifting into neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected locking and unlocking of doors can cause distraction, inconvenience, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front driver-side door independently locks and unlocks while driving
without any warning or apparent cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and even fatalities, as the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly, making it difficult for the driver to control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without pressing the throttle
the vehicle accelerates hard even when tapping the brake
the vehicle rolls backwards or forwards unexpectedly
the vehicle crashes into other objects or vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backwards or forwards unexpectedly
the vehicle fails to engage into gear
the vehicle slips out of gear
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations.
